The paper deals with the problem of finding optimal coded transmissions from two senders to multiple receivers, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The problem involves side-information at the receivers (cs.NI) and fully-participated interactions (cs.SI). The paper also provides code constructions and proof techniques, which are related to distributed systems (cs.DS) and optimization (cs.LG).
